The paper focuses on personalized recommendation using knowledge graphs, which involves techniques from artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed framework also involves attention mechanisms (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR) to extract and encode relevant subgraphs from the knowledge graph. Finally, the paper evaluates the framework on real-world datasets, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
